other_tests.findings: The right-sided PICC line appears to terminate in the right atrium; pulling the catheter back 2 cm will ensure that the tip is in the distal third of the SVC. Lung volumes are slightly low but better expanded compared to the previous study; less crowding of the pulmonary vasculature and improved bibasilar atelectasis. Cardiomediastinal contours are stable. No pleural effusions and no pneumothorax.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Lungs appear better expanded compared to the previous study; there is less crowding of the pulmonary vasculature and improved bibasilar atelectasis.
